name: Commissioned Portrait Vignette
description:
PRICE IS PER SUBJECT SO FOR MORE THAN ONE SUBJECT USE THE QUANTITY PROMT ON THE ITEM IN YOUR CART.

To purchase a commissioned individual portrait vignette from a photo please select the type/size and purchase.  Ryan will reach out to you personally for the digital image and any specific requirements.  

A portrait vignette is a less formal solution to portraiture than a fully resolved painting. The face is completely developed but the majority of the painting varies in its degree of finish.

Satisfaction is guaranteed.  You loving your portrait is the only thing that matters.

TO SPEAK DIRECTLY WITH THE RYAN USE THE CONTACT LINK ON THE LEFT.

name: Sand Plants
description:
Nothing more tropical than when plants grow straight up to the sand.

To quote a client who put it perfectly, "You know what I really like about sand plants? They certainly didn't choose the easy road. They must have really wanted that view. There are plenty of places with rich soil and plenty of rain. But they wanted to watch the waves every day and they adapted to make it happen."

name: In and Out
description: Shifting tides at Torrey Pines beach in San Diego.

name: Blue Eyes
description:
"'Blue Eyes' is a digital painting inspired by the minimalist graphite drawings I have been seeing a lot of recently.  The reference photo was another photograph that had been in my archives for a while prior to finding it's way back to the top of the stack.  

The expression is what I wanted to capture using as little as possible.  Love the contrasting tones between the blue and pastel pink/purple."
- Ryan

name: 15th Street
description:
"15th street is a digital abstraction of an image that I've loved for years.  This particular intersection represents everything that San Diego has to offer; beach, views, sun, women in bikinis, and of course waves.  With the views from La Jolla to San Clemente this is my favorite red light in the county.

From this particular spot you can see the beautiful intersection between the wealthy socialite and the teenage beach bums and all the variations of status, lifestyle, and ethnicity."
- Ryan

Limited edition of 10 16x20 gallery wrapped prints.

Each print is signed and numbered by Ryan.

name: Torrey Pines Almond
description:
"This image was taken at my home break, Torrey Pines, in San Diego on a small winter morning with a great offshore breeze.  This view is one only a surfer knows.  The perspective from the water transports me to the spot every time I look at it.

The allure of Torrey Pines is the magic of the sun peaking over the Torrey Pines reserve illuminating the fog and warming your back as you wait for the next set.  This was one of those mornings."
- Ryan

name: Wave
description:
"Wave is a digital abstraction of another photograph I took from the water.  I particularly like this image because of the perfect shape of the wave and it's ability to make the viewer feel small in proportion.  The abstraction builds a layer of geometry to an otherwise fluid subject and provides the viewer with a multi-layer visual.  

I love looking at this image because I see something new every time."
-Ryan

name: Green Bench
description: What a beautifully serene and lonely bench on one of the most beautiful beaches in the world on Lani, HI

name: Moonrise over the Bay
description:
"One of those right place/right time moments.  Beautiful spectacle to see the moon rising illuminated by the sunset.

You can almost feel the frigid air just by looking at this image."
- Ryan

name: Speed Blur - Original
description:
Original oil on canvas 11x14.  Painted in April 2013.

"I have always been a fan of the images in surf magazines that show the surfer flying down the line appearing to go faster than the camera can capture leaving everything but the surfer out of focus.  These images freeze time, highlight the subject by placing them in focus, and give the whole image a sense of speed and motion.

With this painting I was trying to replicate that sense of motion and smooth blurriness in those images.  Placing the wave against a sunset allowed for those beautiful abstraction of light and the transparent nature of the wave."
- Ryan

name: Sunset Palms
description:
"This image of hawaiian sunset with silhouetted palms was taken on the west side of Maui, HI, and holds a special place in my personal life.

This photograph was taken on the trip to Hawaii when I got engaged to my beautiful, smart, loving wife.  I don't know if the sunsets were especially beautiful that trip or if I was floating on cloud nine, but more incredible images came from this trip than any other trip since."
- Ryan

name: Liquid Surfer
description:
"I had this original photograph in my archives of a stand up paddle boarder in Del Mar, CA hanging five with such a clean style and was constantly drawn to over and over again.  The original image wasn't anything to write home about so it sat in the archives for almost three years.

One day I was looking at it and started toying with my painting application using it as a reference.  Modified this, contrast that, make a few lines here, few lines there, done...and I loved it!  I cleaned it up and put a bow on it.  Sometime simplicity is the key."
- Ryan

name: The Look
description:
"This image a result of the lesson I learned from 'Liquid Surfer' to try to embrace simplicity.  You don't have to sacrifice quality, style or emotion by using simple and almost impulsive techniques.

'The Look' is a digital painting I did trying to capture emotion and feeling using very loose and quick stokes.  The result is a very intrusive image that makes the viewer feel like they were the intended recipient of the look."
- Ryan

name: Lighthouse
description:
"Ever look under the golden gate bridge?  There is this old tower, that is out in the elements, alone.  From the water there is a POW/MIA flag in the window.  Very moving to see up close and person such a hauntingly lonely tower displaying a similarly haunting image in it's windows.

Even the consistently trustworthy google search didn't provide any more clarity to it's purpose."
- Ryan

name: Life Guard Tower
description:
"This image of this beautifully illuminated life guard tower on the west side of Maui, HI, holds a special place in my personal life just like 'Sunset Palms.'

This photograph was taken on the trip to Hawaii when I got engaged to my beautiful, smart, loving wife.  I don't know if the sunsets were especially beautiful that trip or if I was floating on cloud nine, but more incredible images came from this trip than any other trip since."
- Ryan

I ran a cross a saying on Pinterest that struck a cord with me that spawned the new image below.  The saying is "Do More of What Makes You Awesome."  What a great perspective on life.
